<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-096-954  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 096 954.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  Feb 27 1989 n237 p13(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New digital data service from Pacific Bell. (Advanced DigitalNetwork) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Killette, Kathleen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Pacific Bell is the first Bell company to offer dedicated, digitalprivate-line service supporting full-duplex, end-to-end digitaldata transport.andP;  The new service, which is called Advanced DigitalNetwork (ADN), is flexible and efficient, having more speeds andfeatures than current digital data services.andP;  It is also lessexpensive.andP;  Separately, The FCC approves the company's proposal tooffer a computer-based electronic-messaging service, which iscalled Connection.andP;  The service is being tested by students andfaculty at the University of Santa Clara and by members of the SanFrancisco Bay Area disabled community.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Pacific Bell (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    D.PJD.andO;Product:   Advanced Digital Network (Computer network)Connection (Electronic mail system).andO;Topic:     Communications Service SuppliersDigital CommunicationsUnited States. Federal Communications CommissionGovernment RegulationElectronic Mail SystemsSanta Clara, University ofHandicapped.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>